evidence_span: Specimen Identification: MA,MB MC,MD, AO, KS, KTA, NF, SM,SM2; Tube Producer: A, B; Parameters: Year of Production, Sponge manufacturer, Ingot diameter, Forging temperature, Beta-quench temperature, Beta-quench diameter, Alpha-forging temperature, Extrusion temperature, Size of extrusion, Total hot reduction, Tubeshell annealing temperature, Pass number of cold reduction, Intermediate annealed temperature, Final reduction, Q-value, Total cold reduction, Final annealing temperature, Autoclave treatment, Tube dimensions

process_step: annealed at 577°C for 3h before corrosion tests; oxide layers removed by mechanical polishing
conditions: refreshed autoclave; autoclave volume 5L; flow rate 2kg/h; temperature sequences: one-step method at 510°C/10.3MPa for 24h or two-step method: prefilming at 410°C/10.3MPa for 8h + nodule sensitization at 510°C/10.3MPa for 16h; test temperature varied 490-530°C; duration varied 8.5-32h
corrosion_data: Weight gains and nodule coverages shown in Fig. 3; almost same results from one-step and two-step methods
